        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 3 at 6:21PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 621 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Thunderbird Colony, or 15 miles northwest of Faulkton, moving south
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brentwood Colony, Thunderbird Colony, Norbeck, Blumengard Colony, and
Loyalton.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
